text: Ekaterina Abramia (, born August 25, 1979 in Tbilisi) is a Georgian rhythmic gymnast. Abramia competed for Georgia in the rhythmic gymnastics individual all-around competition at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. There she was 25th in the qualification round and did not advance to the semifinal. == References == == External links == * * Category:1979 births Category:Living people Category:Rhythmic gymnasts from Georgia (country) Category:Gymnasts at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic gymnasts of Georgia (country) Category:Sportspeople from Tbilisi
